&lt;p&gt;Locum Consultant in Anaesthetics and Intensive Care Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will join a department of over 40 Consultants and 35 Associate Specialist/ Speciality Doctors and trainees. The department is very active in many areas of clinical practice, and offers a pivotal role in service delivery throughout the organisation. There are opportunities to develop individual specialist interests, and to become part of a team who take quality in care, and excellence in education and teaching, as priorities. The successful applicant will be welcomed as a full and active member of a very open group who are working hard to ensure continuity across a number of clinical sites. Anaesthetic services at Eastbourne cover major urology surgery including laparoscopic robotic cases, ENT, orthopaedics, ophthalmology and nontheatre work including paediatric MRI, ECT, GI endoscopy and cardiology. Conquest Hospital anaesthetic services cover elective and emergency JobDes/Consultants/Anaesthesia/ICM JD Updated August 2020 general surgery, including major colorectal surgery, breast surgery, obstetrics, gynaecology, trauma and orthopaedics, ENT and non-theatre work including interventional radiology, MRI, cardiology and GI endoscopy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Critical Care at ESHT comprises 8 mixed medical and surgical level 2/3 beds at Eastbourne with 11 mixed medical and surgical beds at Conquest site. This is made up of 6 level 3 beds and 5 level 2 beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr James EvansJob titleLead Clinician for Intensive CareTelephone number0300 131 4500&lt;/p&gt;
